{"type":"message","id":"b41faa27","parentId":"b34d13cf","timestamp":"2026-03-25T08:47:18.861Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user 弗尼 (Fernie) sent a message in a group chat saying \"挺好，以后农历两个字也可以不写\" which translates to \"Pretty good, from now on the two characters for lunar calendar can also be omitted.\"\n\nThis seems to be referring to some previous conversation or context about displaying dates or lunar calendar information. Since I was mentioned (was_mentioned: true), they're likely giving me feedback or instructions.\n\nHowever, I don't have context about what they're referring to - this seems to be a continuation of a previous conversation that I don't have access to. They're saying it's fine to not write \"农历\" (lunar calendar) characters in the future.\n\nSince I was mentioned and this seems to be giving me feedback or instructions, I should respond. But I don't have context about what specifically they're talking about. I should acknowledge this and perhaps ask for clarification if needed, or just acknowledge that I've noted their preference.\n\nGiven that this is a group chat and I should be concise and natural, I'll keep my response brief.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"收到，记住了 👍 以后显示农历时可以省略\"农历\"这两个字，直接用日期就行。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"glm-4-7-251222","usage":{"input":5858,"output":464,"cacheRead":11328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17650,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774428432624}}
